EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to peace officers; authorizing a law enforcement
agency to require applicants for certain positions of
employment to make certain attestations concerning
cannabis as a condition precedent to employment; and
providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law prohibits a law enforcement agency from requiring a peace officer
2 to provide an oral or written attestation concerning any use of cannabis by the
3 peace officer that occurred at any time before the peace officer submitted his or her
4 application for employment with the law enforcement agency as a condition
5 precedent to employment as a peace officer. (NRS 289.030) This bill authorizes a
6 law enforcement agency to require an applicant seeking a position of employment
7 for which the applicant would be authorized or required to possess or carry a
8 firearm to provide such an attestation concerning any use of cannabis by the
9 applicant that occurred in the 12 months immediately preceding the date on which
10 the applicant submitted his or her application for employment.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
